data.name: Any%
data.rules:
Starting in New Game, defeat the game as quickly as possible in one segment.
It is not allowed to quit out and reload the save-file.

Full video proof is a requirement.

The use of the cutscene skip glitch with photo mode is not allowed.

Runs use the In-Game Timer (IGT) as the primary timing convention. In order to submit a run with the In-Game Timer, you must let the credits play and navigate to the main menu after the credits to display your In-Game Time. You must also include difficulty select in the beginning of your submission video.

RTA is the secondary timing method and is not required. Submitting RTA only is allowed but the run will be placed below those with IGT. Timing starts upon selecting difficulty.  Timing ends when the final cutscene triggers after Wander enters the pool.

When submitting runs, please do not include milliseconds in your time. That slot exists solely for individual time attack submissions.

data.name: All Main Missions Vanilla
data.rules:
All Main Missions Vanilla - timing starts from pressing continue on The Man with the Guardian Spirit and ends in the blackscreen after pressing "Go forward" on John Dee's body in The Queen's Eyes. (NG+ Samurai runs omit The Man with the Guardian Spirit).

The times will be split between platforms (PC and PS4). PC uses the LiveSplit RTA no load plugin made by B3LYP and PS4 will use RTA. All runs must have video with decent quality. Manual pausing of the timer is disallowed. PC runs require RTA no load timer to be shown throughout the run. Runs must be done offline to disable accumulated clan buffs (clan inheriting is allowed) [does not apply to NG+ or individual level runs]. PC is current patch (CP) and PS4 is either 1.00 or CP.

data.name: Any% No TearDrop
data.rules:
``Objective``

Beat the game as fast as possible.
This category does not allow the use of the [**TearDrop**](https://wiki.speedsouls.com/darksouls3:TearDrop) glitch. 

Except for the [**TearDrop**](https://wiki.speedsouls.com/darksouls3:TearDrop) glitch, there are no additional restrictions on how the player completes the game. They must simply start a new character and beat the game as quickly as they can.

Glitches, Skips and Sequence Breaks are all allowed. Using other programs to alter or affect the game or even modify the game code is not allowed.

This category uses all available glitches and is run on Patch that is the fastest. (VER 1.08). Check the [**Downpatching**](https://wiki.speedsouls.com/darksouls3:Downpatching) page on how to downpatch your game to an older version.

[**Any%**](https://wiki.speedsouls.com/darksouls3:Any%25) is a different category.

* You may kill as many or as few bosses as you want before finishing the game.

data.name: Beat the game
data.rules: Timing begins when you press start at the title screen and ends on the final beat of the ending jingle.

data.name: All Bosses (No DLC)
data.rules:
``Objective``

Defeat all main game bosses and beat the game. (No DLC bosses). The boss order does not matter but a requirement is that the first flame gets linked somewhere in the run. 

Glitches, Skips and Sequence Breaks are all allowed. Using other programs to alter or affect the game or even modify the game code is not allowed.

This category uses all available glitches and is run on App ver. 1.12 / Regulation ver. 1.31 or further.

data.name: Any%
data.rules:
Difficulty: Tomb Raider
Time: The scoreboard is sorted by Times without Loads - load remover available via LiveSplit for PC runs. Console runs are sorted by real Time.
FPS: If you are doing glitched runs, FPS MUST be limited to 100 (using DXtory or RivaTuner) AND shown in your video.
Load Times: Only submit no loads time for PC runs! Leave blank for Console runs.
Timer: MUST be shown in your video if you are doing PC runs!

Timer starts when you've pressed "A" in the Combat Difficulty Menu.
Timer ends when you reach the double doors and activate the cinematic trigger. (after you've killed the boss)

You need to have the "Remnant Resistance" DLC enabled if you do pistol skip or you will not get a pistol and cannot finish a run.

The following is not allowed in Glitchless runs:
1) Consecutive AX Climbing
2) Skywalking (when triggered manually)
3) Airwalking
4) Aim Clipping
5) Jump roll clipping
6) Melee clipping
7) Melee slide
8​) Clipping by picking up items
9) Melee attacks and/or rolling on slippery slopes canceling the sliding animation
10) Clipping by jumping and holding forward
11) Long jump (Ninja jump in syria)
12) Boosted jump off of climbable walls
13) Activating campfires during a cutscene, or whilst dead
14) Ghost walking
15) Vault Clipping
16) The "Arrow Dynamics" trick
17) The "Swag Strats" trick
18) The "Pistol OOB"
19) Rope Boosting
